   5:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/BSP/STM32N6xx_Nucleo/stm32n6xx_nucleo_xspi.c ****   * @brief   This file includes a standard driver for the XSPI
   6:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/BSP/STM32N6xx_Nucleo/stm32n6xx_nucleo_xspi.c ****   *          memories mounted on STM32N6XX_NUCLEO board.
   7:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/BSP/STM32N6xx_Nucleo/stm32n6xx_nucleo_xspi.c ****   @verbatim
   8:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/BSP/STM32N6xx_Nucleo/stm32n6xx_nucleo_xspi.c ****   ==============================================================================
   9:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/BSP/STM32N6xx_Nucleo/stm32n6xx_nucleo_xspi.c ****                      ##### How to use this driver #####
  10:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/BSP/STM32N6xx_Nucleo/stm32n6xx_nucleo_xspi.c ****   ==============================================================================
  11:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/BSP/STM32N6xx_Nucleo/stm32n6xx_nucleo_xspi.c ****   [..]
  12:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/BSP/STM32N6xx_Nucleo/stm32n6xx_nucleo_xspi.c ****    (#) This driver is used to drive the MX25UM51245G Octal NOR
  13:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/BSP/STM32N6xx_Nucleo/stm32n6xx_nucleo_xspi.c ****        external memories mounted on STM32N6XX_NUCLEO board.
  14:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/BSP/STM32N6xx_Nucleo/stm32n6xx_nucleo_xspi.c **** 
  15:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/BSP/STM32N6xx_Nucleo/stm32n6xx_nucleo_xspi.c ****    (#) This driver need specific component driver (MX25UM51245G) to be included with.
  16:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/BSP/STM32N6xx_Nucleo/stm32n6xx_nucleo_xspi.c **** 
  17:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/BSP/STM32N6xx_Nucleo/stm32n6xx_nucleo_xspi.c ****    (#) MX25UM51245G Initialization steps:
  18:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/BSP/STM32N6xx_Nucleo/stm32n6xx_nucleo_xspi.c ****        (++) Initialize the OPSI external memory using the BSP_XSPI_NOR_Init() function. This
  19:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/BSP/STM32N6xx_Nucleo/stm32n6xx_nucleo_xspi.c ****             function includes the MSP layer hardware resources initialization and the
  20:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/BSP/STM32N6xx_Nucleo/stm32n6xx_nucleo_xspi.c ****             XSPI interface with the external memory.
  21:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/BSP/STM32N6xx_Nucleo/stm32n6xx_nucleo_xspi.c **** 
  22:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/BSP/STM32N6xx_Nucleo/stm32n6xx_nucleo_xspi.c ****    (#) MX25UM51245G Octal NOR memory operations
  23:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/BSP/STM32N6xx_Nucleo/stm32n6xx_nucleo_xspi.c ****        (++) XSPI memory can be accessed with read/write operations once it is
  24:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/BSP/STM32N6xx_Nucleo/stm32n6xx_nucleo_xspi.c ****             initialized.
  25:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/BSP/STM32N6xx_Nucleo/stm32n6xx_nucleo_xspi.c ****             Read/write operation can be performed with AHB access using the functions
  26:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/BSP/STM32N6xx_Nucleo/stm32n6xx_nucleo_xspi.c ****             BSP_XSPI_NOR_Read()/BSP_XSPI_NOR_Write().
  27:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/BSP/STM32N6xx_Nucleo/stm32n6xx_nucleo_xspi.c ****        (++) The function BSP_XSPI_NOR_GetInfo() returns the configuration of the XSPI memory.
  28:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/BSP/STM32N6xx_Nucleo/stm32n6xx_nucleo_xspi.c ****             (see the XSPI memory data sheet)
  29:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/BSP/STM32N6xx_Nucleo/stm32n6xx_nucleo_xspi.c ****        (++) Perform erase block operation using the function BSP_XSPI_NOR_Erase_Block() and by
  30:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/BSP/STM32N6xx_Nucleo/stm32n6xx_nucleo_xspi.c ****             specifying the block address. You can perform an erase operation of the whole
  31:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/BSP/STM32N6xx_Nucleo/stm32n6xx_nucleo_xspi.c ****             chip by calling the function BSP_XSPI_NOR_Erase_Chip().
  32:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/BSP/STM32N6xx_Nucleo/stm32n6xx_nucleo_xspi.c ****        (++) The function BSP_XSPI_NOR_GetStatus() returns the current status of the XSPI memory.
  33:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/BSP/STM32N6xx_Nucleo/stm32n6xx_nucleo_xspi.c ****             (see the XSPI memory data sheet)
  34:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/BSP/STM32N6xx_Nucleo/stm32n6xx_nucleo_xspi.c ****        (++) The memory access can be configured in memory-mapped mode with the call of
  35:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/BSP/STM32N6xx_Nucleo/stm32n6xx_nucleo_xspi.c ****             function BSP_XSPI_NOR_EnableMemoryMapped(). To go back in indirect mode, the
  36:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/BSP/STM32N6xx_Nucleo/stm32n6xx_nucleo_xspi.c ****             function BSP_XSPI_NOR_DisableMemoryMapped() should be used.
  37:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/BSP/STM32N6xx_Nucleo/stm32n6xx_nucleo_xspi.c ****        (++) The erase operation can be suspend and resume with using functions
  38:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/BSP/STM32N6xx_Nucleo/stm32n6xx_nucleo_xspi.c ****             BSP_XSPI_NOR_SuspendErase() and BSP_XSPI_NOR_ResumeErase()
  39:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/BSP/STM32N6xx_Nucleo/stm32n6xx_nucleo_xspi.c ****        (++) It is possible to put the memory in deep power-down mode to reduce its consumption.
  40:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/BSP/STM32N6xx_Nucleo/stm32n6xx_nucleo_xspi.c ****             For this, the function BSP_XSPI_NOR_EnterDeepPowerDown() should be called. To leave
  41:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/BSP/STM32N6xx_Nucleo/stm32n6xx_nucleo_xspi.c ****             the deep power-down mode, the function BSP_XSPI_NOR_LeaveDeepPowerDown() should be call
  42:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/BSP/STM32N6xx_Nucleo/stm32n6xx_nucleo_xspi.c ****        (++) The function BSP_XSPI_NOR_ReadID() returns the identifier of the memory
  43:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/BSP/STM32N6xx_Nucleo/stm32n6xx_nucleo_xspi.c ****             (see the XSPI memory data sheet)
  44:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/BSP/STM32N6xx_Nucleo/stm32n6xx_nucleo_xspi.c ****        (++) The configuration of the interface between peripheral and memory is done by
  45:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/BSP/STM32N6xx_Nucleo/stm32n6xx_nucleo_xspi.c ****             the function BSP_XSPI_NOR_ConfigFlash(), three modes are possible :
  46:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/BSP/STM32N6xx_Nucleo/stm32n6xx_nucleo_xspi.c ****             - SPI : instruction, address and data on one line
  47:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/BSP/STM32N6xx_Nucleo/stm32n6xx_nucleo_xspi.c ****             - STR OPI : instruction, address and data on eight lines with sampling on one edge of c
  48:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/BSP/STM32N6xx_Nucleo/stm32n6xx_nucleo_xspi.c ****             - DTR OPI : instruction, address and data on eight lines with sampling on both edgaes o
  49:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/BSP/STM32N6xx_Nucleo/stm32n6xx_nucleo_xspi.c **** 
  50:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/BSP/STM32N6xx_Nucleo/stm32n6xx_nucleo_xspi.c ****   @endverbatim
